    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="584"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/708</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-22">July 22,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chinese Minister informed me in strict confidence that he has a confidential
                    message from the Chinese Minister of Finance inquiring informally and
                    confidentially when the Chinese Government may “hope to know of the designation
                    of an American financial adviser”, inasmuch as the British financial adviser is
                    to arrive in September. The Minister of Finance says that the people in China
                    attach great importance to American cooperation. He refers to the American
                    Government’s message of February 26 which intimated a desire of international
                    cooperation. He requests that this inquiry be treated as strictly
                    confidential.</p>
                <p>I stated to the Minister that no decision had as yet been arrived at.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
